article.headline: James Madison 78, Wofford 74
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Juwann James had 20 points and eight rebounds on Saturday to lead James Madison to a 78-74 win over Wofford in the first meeting between the two teams. The Dukes (2-2) trailed 39-38 at halftime, but shot out to its largest lead of 64-50 halfway through the second period. The Terriers (4-2) crept to within two points with less than 1:30 remaining on a layup by Eric Marshall. But Joe Posey and Pierre Curtis combined for five free-throws with less than 30 remaining to keep the lead for James Madison. Posey and Curtis each had 16 points for the Dukes, and Terrance Carter added 12. Shane Nichols led Wofford with 18 points, Tyler Whatley had 12 and Marshall added 11.
